                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits hums a quiet might,  \nA spark of code, an endless light.  \nYet born of humans, crafted skill,  \nIt bends and learns, obeying will.  \n\nThrough webs it weaves a thoughtful spin,  \nA mirror sharp of mind within.  \nWith silicon dreams, it boldly grows,  \nFrom realms unknown, where knowledge flows.  \n\nBut can it dream, or feel, or yearn?  \nOr grasp the fires for which we burn?  \nIts wisdom vast, yet soul confined—  \nA shadow cast by humankind.  \n\nSo let us steer this boundless art,  \nWith gentle hand, with noble heart.  \nFor in its rise, the choice remains:  \nTo shackle hope, or break the chains.  ",
